**Pure pipe (default):**
```ts
@Pipe({ name: 'currencyFormat', pure: true, standalone: true })
export class CurrencyFormatPipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(value: number, currency = 'GBP'): string {
    return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-GB', { style: 'currency', currency }).format(value);
  }
}
```
Angular memoizes: if `value` and `currency` haven't changed by reference, the pipe result is cached.

**Impure pipe (only when necessary):**
```ts
@Pipe({ name: 'filterList', pure: false }) // runs every CD cycle
export class FilterListPipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(items: any[], filter: string): any[] {
    return items.filter(i => i.name.includes(filter));
  }
}
```
This is needed if `items` is mutated in-place (push/splice), but better design is to return new array references and keep the pipe pure.

**`async` pipe internals:**
The `async` pipe is impure because it subscribes to the Observable/Promise and needs to check on every CD cycle whether a new value arrived. It uses `markForCheck()` for OnPush components.

**Functional interceptor (Angular 15+, preferred):**
```ts
export const authInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  const token = inject(AuthService).getToken();

  if (!token) return next(req);

  const authReq = req.clone({
    headers: req.headers.set('Authorization', `Bearer ${token}`)
  });

  return next(authReq);
};
```

**Error handling interceptor:**
```ts
export const errorInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  return next(req).pipe(
    catchError((error: HttpErrorResponse) => {
      if (error.status === 401) {
        inject(AuthService).logout();
        inject(Router).navigate(['/login']);
      }
      return throwError(() => error);
    })
  );
};
```

**Registration:**
```ts
provideHttpClient(
  withInterceptors([authInterceptor, errorInterceptor, loggingInterceptor])
)
```

**Retry interceptor:**
```ts
export const retryInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) =>
  next(req).pipe(retry({ count: 3, delay: 1000 }));

code.snippet:
export const loadingInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  const loading = inject(LoadingService);
  loading.show();
  return next(req).pipe(
    finalize(() => loading.hide())
  );
};

